# Commit Message Format
#
# This repository uses Conventional Commits specification:
# <type>: <description>
#
# [optional body]
#
# [optional footer(s)]
#
# Types:
#   feat:     A new feature
#   fix:      A bug fix
#   chore:    Routine tasks, maintenance, or minor changes
#   refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   docs:     Documentation only changes
#   test:     Adding or correcting tests
#   style:    Changes that don't affect code meaning (formatting, etc.)
#
# Examples:
#   feat: add user authentication
#   fix: prevent duplicate goal creation
#   chore: update dependencies
#   docs: add README section on deployment
#
# The commit-msg hook will automatically normalize plain messages:
#   "Add new feature" → "feat: new feature"
#   "Fix bug in calendar" → "fix: bug in calendar"
#   "Remove old config" → "chore: old config"
#   "Rename helper method" → "refactor: helper method"
#
